claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: Journal header page showing the Elsevier logo, a note that contents are available at ScienceDirect, the journal title 'Vaccine', the journal homepage URL, and a cover image of the Vaccine journal. does not support the claim because the image contains only journal header information and no data or statements regarding mutations in cell- or egg-based flu vaccines.
